President Trump and several governors and experts gathered in the Roosevelt Room to discuss prison reform. The President highlighted the importance of promoting public safety and helping former prisoners reintegrate into society. He emphasized the need for job training, mentoring, and drug addiction treatment to break the cycle of recidivism. The governors shared successful reform initiatives in their respective states, such as improving the juvenile justice system and providing job training and professional licenses to inmates. The Attorney General mentioned the need for better spending on reentry and job-training programs in the federal prison system. The participants expressed optimism about the potential of prison reform to reduce crime and provide opportunities for former inmates.